Diagnosis.
Body dark reddish brown (
Fig. 27
); eye in dorsal view 1.2 × as long as temple (
Fig. 28I
); eye in lateral view 1.2 × higher than wide (
Fig. 28K
); frons smooth posteriorly, but rugose between and around antennal sockets (
Fig. 28I
); vertex and temple smooth; face densely granulate and with some long setae near eye, 1.8 × wider than high, rather convex medially and with a longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 28J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 28J
); precoxal sulcus narrowly crenulate, reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 28C
); notauli incomplete, absent on disc (
Fig. 28C
); medio-posterior depression deep and linear, not extending to middle of mesoscutum (
Fig. 28D
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent (
Fig. 28E
); pterostigma 3.7 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 28A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 28N
); length of first tergite 1.3 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae united submedially (
Fig. 28E
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.3 × as long as fore wing (as total visible part), and almost equal to hind tibia (
Fig. 28H
); antenna and metasoma (except black first tergite) brown; palpi and legs (but dorsal side of femur and apical of hind tibia and whole hind tarsus dark brownish) pale yellow (
Fig. 27
).

