subSubSection.paragraph:
Head. Transverse, width of head 1.9 × its lateral length, and 1.5 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 28I
); antenna with 34 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.4 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere3.3, 2.0 and 1.4 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 28G
); length of maxillary palp 1.6 × height of head (
Fig. 28K
); eye in dorsal view 1.2 × as long as temple (
Fig. 28I
); eye in lateral view 1.2 × higher than wide (
Fig. 28K
); frons smooth posteriorly, but rugose between and around antennal sockets (
Fig. 28I
); vertex and temple smooth; OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 16:5:7; face densely granulate and with some long setae near eye, 1.8 × wider than high, rather convex medially and with a longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 28J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 28J
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 28L
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped (
Fig. 28M
), middle tooth curved and acute, with little incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 28L
), medial length of mandible 1.5 × its maximum width.

Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.5 × its height (
Fig. 28C
); pronope absent; medio-anteriorly pronotum crenulate, remainder of pronotum smooth; epicnemial area crenulated ventrally, remainder smooth (
Fig. 28C
); precoxal sulcus narrowly crenulate, reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area; pleural sulcus narrowly crenulated ventrally, remainder smooth (
Fig. 28C
); episternal scrobe linear and deep; metapleuron reticulate-rugose ventrally, remainder smooth (
Fig. 28C
); notauli incomplete, absent on disc (
Fig. 28D
); medioposterior depression deep and linear shaped, not extending to middle of mesoscutum, scutellar sulcus deep, with three longitudinal carinae, sulcus 2.5 × wider than its maximum length (
Fig. 28D
); scutellum smooth; surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent (
Fig. 28E
).

Wings (
Figs 28A–B
). Pterostigma wide, 3.7 × longer than its maximum width. r:3-SR:SR1 = 5:17:55; 1-SR+M slightly sinuate; SR1 straight; r 0.6 × as long as width of pterostigma; cu-a postfurcal; 1-CU1:2-CU1 = 3: 20; 3- CU1 as long as CU1b; 2-SR:3-SR:r-m = 20:21:11; m-cu interstitial, converging to 1-M posteriorly; first subdiscal cell 3.6 × as long as wide; M+CU1 sclerotized. Hind wing: M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 20:15:13; m-cu weakly antefurcal.

Legs. Hind coxa smooth, without ventro-basal tubercle; tarsal claws slender, longer than arolium (
Fig. 28N
); length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 4.4, 9.2 and 6.7 × their width, respectively; apical appendages of hind tarsal segments absent, segments ventrally with dense bristles (
Fig. 28N
).

Metasoma. Length of first tergite 1.3 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae united submedially (
Fig. 28E
); dorsope distinct; convexity of upper valve of ovipositor small and with inconspicuous notch (
Fig. 28H
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.3 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.3 times), and almost as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 28H
).

Colour. Dark reddish brown (
Fig. 27
); antenna and metasoma (but first tergite black) brown; palpi and legs (except dorsal side of femur and apical of hind tibia and whole hind tarsus dark brownish) pale yellow; pterostigma and veins brown, wing membrane hyaline.
